The Magician is composed of mainly two offensive parts: the caster's Direct Damage and the pet. The pet, as you probably already know, is the strongest pet out of all the pets. The Mage's direct damage is also very strong - the Wizard's is the strongest with the Mage/Druid sort of tied for second and third. Magicians also have strong Area effect spells (although they are not too useful) and the best bolts (which takes sometime getting used to, but they are pretty useful). Magician is also a very good soloing class, and they can add much to the group (they deal a large amount of damage to mobs).<br>
<br>
Drawbacks: <br>
1) a lot of the summoning spells aren't that useful, especially with the fact that they go poof when you log off or go Link Dead.<br>
2) mages actually don't have a very good name (well at least from what I've seen so far), people are always blaming mage pets for breaking mez and yes I've seen a lot of mages when they are in a group, all they do is send in their pet - they don't even blast. And also some mages use Earthpet in a group etc...generally people don't realize the mage's true power because they never grouped with a good mage. Your challenge is to make a good name for yourself, and perferrably for the class <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
3) Mages have next to no escape spells (no root/snare, etc) This makes the mage class much harder to survive. However that is not to say they CAN'T survive, just more difficult <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Many mages complain about their class relative to the Necromancer class - so think thoroughly about which class are you going to make <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
4) Magicians only get 2 line of Direct Damage spells: Magic and Fire. Both Druids and Wizards have all three lines of DD (magic, cold, and fire). This isn't a big deal most of the time, but in some situations you may wish you had a cold based spell.<br>
<br>
Personally for me, I never regreted that I am a Magician. I loved this class from the beginning. Before my Mage I also made a ecro - played him for a little then realized that it's just not my style. Made a mage afterwards and now he's lvl 51 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  (still stuck in Hate...God please grant me the Robe!)<br>
<br>
My recommendation is that experience a little bit with each class, and find which one suits your style. But if you just want to stay with one class - the Mage won't dissapoint you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
-Extra <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uezno.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ezno</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/posticons/eyes.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 275<br> <font color=#333333>(12/4/00 5:08:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New guy - confused</span><hr size=1> <br>
If you dig deep you will see that every class has its  &quot;complaints&quot;  and &quot;complainers&quot;.   <br>
<br>
Magicians are an excellent choice to play.  They provide a lot of fun and a lot of variety.  They will give you the chance to group up with other players or solo as you wish.   My suggestion is to not worry as much what other players think about a class and, instead, try the class out for a bit to see if you like it.   Each class has its strengths and weaknesses.  There will always be spells/abilities in the game that make you think &quot;damn, I wish I could do *that*&quot;.  The key is to realize that the person that can do *that* can't do everything and there are things that  your class can do better than they can (or they might not be able to do it at all).  <br>
<br>
There are six classes in the game that get a &quot;pet&quot;.  Of these, only two are considered &quot;pet&quot; classes (Magician and Necromancer).   Enchanters get a very limited pet but have the ability to charm creatures as well (making them pets for a short duration).   Shamans get a weak wolf pet once they hit high level.  Shadowknights get a scaled down version of the Necromancer pet.   Druids are able to charm animals to use as pets for a very short duration.    (I don't count Bards since their charm only lasts for 6 seconds).  <br>
<br>
Of all of these classes, the Magician gets the most variety of pets and has the most overall powerful pets.<br>
<br>
There will always be things that other classes can do that you might think would be cool. (I came to a Magician after playing a druid and I always missed SoW and Ports) but you have to realize that they can't do everything either (I would miss my pet if I played a druid).   <p> <br>
