<br>
As a female player, you will enjoy a lot of freebies from the gentlemen of Everquest. Guys will sooner give you free SoWs, Clarities, SMRs or whatever, than they would ever give me. Sometimes my wife and I would be camping druids, when a player who was passing through would clarity her and continue on his way, leaving me sitting there right next to her, pouting. In this respect, the life of a female EQ player is very pleasant.<br>
<br>
Then there is the downside, the male jerks of Everquest. Rather than celebrating a woman in their midst, they ridicule her or try to take advantage of her. When my wife played a wood elf ranger, she would occasionally get &quot;cyber-propositioned.&quot; Also on this end of the spectrum are what my wife terms the &quot;weirdos of EQ.&quot; These are the guys who you've grouped with maybe a couple times, and they start confiding their RL secrets, or talking about their problems in RL that you don't care about. &quot;Yeah yeah your wife left you because you play too much EQ, go pull something.&quot;<br>
<br>
I'm not trying to scare you away, because the more women who play EQ, the better, IMO. Just be prepared to deal with some of the special treatment you'll probably receive, both good and bad. <br>
<br>
