<br>
I would first like to clarify a few posts about you being a female and playing in EverQuest.  Yes, there are a lot less of us females than males and while you may get treated kinder than males I have never had someone send me a private message asking to cyber sex or any @#%$ like that.  Sure, I have had a few people make some comments that were somewhat sexual but it was in fun and we both laughed about it.  Also, so many males play female characters that most people think you probably are a male until they get to know you, I know I look at most of the female characters out there like that.  Be a female, be proud of who we are. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Now to the good stuff!  Magicians are a class that rely on there pet, and we have a very hard time doing anything without our pet.  We have very few spells that help other people other than summoning food, water, lightsources, minor weapons and such.  We can also cast invisable on ourselves and other people, as well as see invisable which can be very helpful at times.  Our best spell which is benifical to others(called Buffs) is our damage shield line of spells.  Well, you might be wondering what a damage shield is huh?  It is a shield that surrounds you so that whenever a monster hits us we inflict damage upon it by a force field type thing around us that is made of fire.  As we increase in levels we can make damage shields that do more damage and last longer.  Other than those few spells we don't really have alot to offer as &quot;Buffs&quot;.<br>
<br>
Like many people have said in this post we are the master class of summoning pets, and we are damn good at it. When we start out in the game we do not get pets right away however.  We have to wait until level 4, which is easy to get, and then we can summon our first line of pets.  We have 4 different choices of pets.<br>
<br>
Earth - Can take alot of damage and keeps the enemy monster is one spot by casting a spell called root.<br>
<br>
Water - This pet has quite a bit of hitpoints and casts a spell which causes cold based damage.<br>
<br>
Air - This pet has less hitpoints than a water pet but can cast a spell that 'stuns' the monster which renders it helpless for a few seconds.<br>
<br>
Fire - This pet has the least amount of hitpoints but causes the most amount of damage through its personal damage shield and fire based spell that it casts against the enemy monster.<br>
<br>
Magician pets are what makes us defining and very powerful.  At the higher levels these pets are brutes and can destroy just about anything in there path and many people will be envious in your power. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    But of course, not having a pet or having it die is a big drawback since most cases you will die if don't have a pet and a big mean monster wants to eat your for a snack.<br>
<br>
Next is our spells which are commonly called 'Nukes' or DD(Direct damage) spells.  These spells when cast upon a monster do damage to them right away.  All through our levels we get upgrades to our nukes which are fire based and magic based.  Most of the time you will have your pet attack the enemy monster and you will stand a bit of ways back and 'nuke' or 'blow up' the monster.  It's fun having a slave and telling what to do. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
So you might be wondering, wow... the magician class seems so powerful! What do I have to loose if I cloose this class?  Well, usually if your pet dies, you will die as well since the only form of 'escape' that we have is to either Gate(teleports us back to our starting location, and takes a long time to cast) or to run!  Running may seem easy but it's hard to out run something if it runs faster than you. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
My suggestions for making a magician when deciding a race.<br>
<br>
Erudite - If you make an erudite put 10 stats into intelligence, 10 into strength and 10 into dexterity.  If you start this character take the boat over to Qeynos and when you finally get to the front gates ask for a 'bind' there.  Your bind point determines where you start if you die.<br>
<br>
Gnome - Put 10 into strength, and 20 into intelligence.  Personally, I think this is the best race to choose.<br>
<br>
Human - Put 25 into intelligence and 5 into dexterity.<br>
<br>
Dark Elf - I would not suggest this race since it is very hard to get around in the starting city, and the starting location has a lot of mean critters running around.  If you must play this race, put 10 into strength, 10 into dexterity and 10 into intelligence.<br>
<br>
High Elf - I will be shamed for saying it but high elves do not make good magicians since there stregth is to low, and have low dexterity.  However there intelligence is good.  If you really want to play this race put 15 into intelligence, 10 into strength and 5 into dexterity.<br>
<br>
While there are more stats than just strength, dexterity, and intelligence I feel that these are the most importaint stats of all for a magician.  Intelligence is the ammount of mana(amount you can cast) which effects how many times you can cast spells before you are OOM(Out of Mana).  Strength is how much weight you can carry and is very importaint because it allows you to carry more treasure or loot around.  Dexterity is what determines if you regain concentration casting a spell say if a  monster starts to whack you rather than your pet, a very importaint stat.<br>
<br>
When you log into the great world of Norrath for the first time, grab the manual you got with your game and use the maps to goto the the casters guild and turn in your guild invitation to get your robes!  While you are there use your right mouse button and click on your master trainer.  A window will pop up that will allow you to train your different skills, you start out with 5 training points and I suggest you put them all into piercing since you start with a dagger*.  After you do this, click on your spells icon and start to scribe in you spell burst of flame and minor shielding.  Always keep a shielding line on spells cast since it gives you extra hitpoints.<br>
<br>
After you have finally memorized your spells goto the newbie starting location and start to attack the critters out there.  When you finally save up enough money buy some backpacks, pouches, etc to carry around more things.  it gets frustrating very fast always having to run back and forth to the merchant every few minutes to sell things.  After you have bough a few backpacks save up all your money for level 4 when you get new spells.  When you finally get level 4 I would suggest you buy the fire or water pet, your next damage spell, summon food, summon water, summon bandages, gate, reclaim energy, true north and summon wisp.<br>
<br>
Well, thats my long hint on how to help you start your career on being a magician. Good luck, and if you ever have questions come back here and ask away. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p><i>Liandriana Sedai 54-Elementalist<br>Syui Chan 48-Monk<br>Caba 20-Shaman</i></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uliandriana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Liandriana</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10> at: 12/6/00 4:42:47 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ureaperrp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ReaperRP</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 213<br> <font color=#333333>(12/16/00 9:27:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Being a magician</span><hr size=1> Dexterity does not affect you recovering from and interuption. All it does is very slightly increase the rate of learning Channeling (The skill that increases recovery chance), and make you proc a tiny little bit more. In my opinion NO points should be spent into Dexterity for any race. <p><html>
